2009-04-02  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, include/libssh2.h: release 1.1

2009-03-31  Daniel Stenberg

	* example/simple/sftp.c, example/simple/sftp_write.c,
	example/simple/sftp_write_nonblock.c: Sofian Brabez removed
	duplicate calls to libssh2_session_set_blocking()

2009-03-31  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: Uh, it is important that we don't set the local
	state 'local.close' to TRUE until _after_ we're done as otherwise we
	might not get called again properly to clean the entire thing since
	the close state is checked in libssh2_channel_free

2009-03-30  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/packet.c: Removed the trace output that said "May block until
	packet of type..." since it simply wasn't true for non-blocking
	operations.

2009-03-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c, src/channel.h, src/sftp.c: made sure the SFTP code
	makes more use of internal non-blocking functions instead of the
	external API entries

2009-03-28  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/userauth.c: Fixed the memory leak in in
	libssh2_userauth_hostbased_fromfile_ex() that Jean-Louis Charton
	found. Additional minor indent and comment edits.

2009-03-28  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/userauth.c: indent changes and removed libssh2_ prefix from
	static function

2009-03-28   Yang Tse

	* src/version.c: include libssh2_priv.h instead of libssh2.h in
	order to get LIBSSH2_API properly defined on LIBSSH2_WIN32 build
	targets

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c, src/channel.h, src/sftp.c: Additional non-blocking
	fixes.

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: Me and my long fingers couldn't resist "merging"
	these statements in a previous commit but of course that broke
	functionality and this is a revert of that change.

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/transport.c: Dump to stderr simply because the other tracing
	functions in misc.c already use stderr and mixing output "channels"
	causes too much confusion for me!

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c, src/channel.h, src/session.c, src/sftp.c: fixed
	sftp_shutdown() for the blockiness and fixed libssh2_channel_close()
	to work properly non-blocking

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h: Fixed the order of the check in the
	BLOCK_ADJUST() macro so that it also works for
	libssh2_session_free()

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* tests/simple.c: kill warnings

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h: Fix the BLOCK_ADJUST_ERRNO() macro to behave
	properly in blocking mode.

2009-03-27  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* configure.in: Add AC_CONFIG_MACRO_DIR to avoid warnings with
	libtool v2.2.x.

2009-03-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/kex.c, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/misc.c, src/session.c,
	src/sftp.c: fix comments, moved to htonu64 function to sftp.c and
	made it static

2009-03-26  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/Makefile.am, src/comp.h, src/kex.c, src/libssh2_priv.h,
	src/mac.c, src/mac.h: More cleaning up converting libssh2_ to
	_libssh2_ for internal functions and removing libssh2_ from static
	functions. Added mac.h.

2009-03-26  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/Makefile.am, src/comp.c, src/comp.h, src/kex.c: comp.c only
	as a single _libssh2_ function, no external one

2009-03-26  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, TODO, docs/Makefile.am,
	docs/libssh2_channel_handle_extended_data.3,
	docs/libssh2_channel_receive_window_adjust.3,
	docs/libssh2_channel_receive_window_adjust2.3,
	docs/libssh2_channel_set_blocking.3, include/libssh2.h,
	src/Makefile.am, src/channel.c, src/channel.h, src/kex.c,
	src/libssh2_priv.h, src/packet.c, src/session.c, src/sftp.c,
	src/transport.c, src/transport.h, src/userauth.c:
	* Renamed the functions in src/transport.c to be _libssh2_transport_
	  prefixed and introduced a transport.h header.

	* Fixed the blocking mode to only change behavior not the actual
	  underlying socket mode so we now always work with non-blocking
	  sockets. This also introduces a new rule of thumb in libssh2 code:
	  we don't call the external function calls internally. We use the
	  internal (non-blocking) ones!

	* libssh2_channel_receive_window_adjust2 was added and
	  libssh2_channel_receive_window_adjust is now deprecated

	* Introduced "local" header files with prototypes etc for different
	  parts instead of cramming everything into libssh2_priv.h. channel.h
	  is the first.

2009-03-25  Daniel Stenberg

	* example/simple/scp_nonblock.c: avoid some busy-looping

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* TODO: one function to remove, one proto to correct

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: Updated comments and removed "libssh2_" prefixes from
	static functions

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_session_get_blocking.3: added basic docs

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_session_flag.3: quite possibly one of the most
	pointless functions in the libssh2 API...a

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/misc.c: ENOTCONN obviously doesn't exist in win32 so don't
	try to map that

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: [no comment]

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: EEK revert the part of the previous commit that
	was just my non-functional attempts to make things work with
	blocking sockets.

2009-03-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/packet.c: I cut out the
	poll_socket argument from the protos for_libssh2_packet_askv() and
	_libssh2_packet_ask() since they are internal and nothing in the
	code base uses that functionality == simplicity with no drawbacks!

2009-03-19  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h, src/misc.c: pass in unsigned ints for u32
	values and not longs

2009-03-19  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/misc.c, src/session.c,
	src/transport.c:
	- (Mar 19 2009) Daniel Stenberg: based on a patch by "E L" we now
	  use errno properly after recv() and send() calls (that internally
	  are now known as _libssh2_recv() and _libssh2_send()) so that the
	  API and more works fine on windows too!

2009-03-18  Daniel Stenberg

	* AUTHORS: I'm upgrading myself!

2009-03-17  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* tests/ssh2.sh: Add StrictModes=no to work around cygwin problem.
	Reported by Yang Tse <yangsita@gmail.com>.

