	Reported by Yang Tse <yangsita@gmail.com>

2009-03-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/packet.c: re-indented for clarity

2009-03-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: re-indented _libssh2_channel_packet_data_len()
	somewhat to make the huge condition somewhat easier on the eye

2009-03-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c, src/comp.c, src/crypt.c, src/hostkey.c, src/kex.c,
	src/libssh2_priv.h, src/mac.c, src/misc.c, src/openssl.h,
	src/packet.c, src/publickey.c, src/scp.c, src/session.c,
	src/sftp.c, src/transport.c, src/userauth.c: A cleanup effort:
	libssh2_ prefixes only on external APIs. Use _libssh2_ prefix for
	library-wide internal functions. Don't use any of those on static
	functions.  I also did some comments and whitespace changes.

2009-03-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* include/libssh2.h: bump packet default size to 32768

2009-03-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_banner_set.3,
	docs/libssh2_channel_direct_tcpip_ex.3,
