	page

2008-12-26  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_base64_decode.3: libssh2_base64_decode is deprecated
	and subject for removal in a future version (like on the next soname
	bump)

2008-12-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/Makefile.am, docs/libssh2_base64_decode.3: wrote up a first
	libssh2_base64_decode man page, added a few missing man pages to the
	tarball

2008-12-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_sftp_rename_ex.3, docs/libssh2_sftp_rmdir_ex.3,
	docs/libssh2_sftp_stat_ex.3, docs/libssh2_sftp_unlink_ex.3,
	docs/libssh2_sftp_write.3: based on Heiner Steven's report, fix the
	name and description of these man pages!

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS: briefly mention my recent sftp-related fixes

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* README: mention web site and mailing list, as I think they're not
	mentioned anywhere else in the package!

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sshentry.c: removed obviously superfluous comments

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/misc.c: use a single >>32 instead of "(value / 65536) /
	65536", just make sure that the shift is done on a 64bit type

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/transport.c: remove unused #ifndef, and two whitespace
	changes

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: style/indent changes only to enforce < 80 column
	lines more strict

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, docs/libssh2_sftp_seek.3, include/libssh2_sftp.h,
	src/sftp.c: libssh2_sftp_seek64() it is now for the 64bit seek
	function too as the seek2 name has never been used in a release and
	it makes the naming consistent

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_session_block_directions.3, include/libssh2.h: 0.19
	is now 1.0

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, docs/libssh2_sftp_tell.3, docs/libssh2_sftp_tell64.3,
	src/sftp.c: Based on Alexander Lamaison's patch, there's now a new
	function called libssh2_sftp_tell64() that returns the 64 bit file
	offset, as the existing libssh2_sftp_tell() only returns a size_t.

2008-12-22  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h, src/sftp.c: first conversion of a malloc =>
	buffer in the sftp handle struct

2008-12-20  Daniel Stenberg

	* libssh2-style.el: helper script for emacs users to get the code
	style done libssh2-style automatically

2008-12-19  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/sftp.c:
	- Markus Moeller fixed the issue also reported by Alexander Lamaison
	  which caused SFTP reads with large buffers to fail.

2008-12-17  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* tests/ssh2.sh: Sshd is slow to start on some systems.

2008-12-17  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h, src/sftp.c: Avoid one malloc by putting the
	entire handle buffer in the handle struct at once, use a define for
	the maximum size length of the handle instead of '256' in the code.

2008-12-16  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: removed some more libssh2_ prefixes from private
	functions

	Made the libssh2_sftp_open_ex() deal with servers that first
	responds with STATUS OK and then sends the actual HANDLE. It seems
	openssh does this at times and it screwed things up. To me it seems
	like a spec violation...

2008-12-16  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/channel.c: removed unused code, intended the code somewhat

2008-12-16  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: Nothing used libssh2_sftp_packet_read's flush
	argument anymore so I removed it and simplified the code somewhat
	thanks to that. I then renamed the function to sftp_packet_read()
	only since it is private in this file anyway.

2008-12-15  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: renamed libssh2_sftp_packet_requirev to plain
	sftp_packet_requirev since it is private in this file only and a
	shorter name is nicer

	Removed a "flush" of the data in sftp_packet_requirev() that now
	seems to have made SFTP operations a lot more reliable. It didn't
	make much sense to have it there but if someone can present a reason
	for one I figure we should carefully investigate one and only do it
	conditionally where/when needed.

2008-12-15  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_sftp_last_error.3: Clarify that this is only fine to
	use after an actual SFTP protocol error return code.

2008-11-27  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* tests/Makefile.am, tests/ssh2.sh: Support EXEEXT in self-test.

2008-11-27  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* configure.in: Cygwin needs -lcrypto for -lssl.  Reported by "Yang
	Tse" <yangsita@gmail.com>.

2008-11-27  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_session_block_directions.3: oops, add missing file

2008-11-26   Yang Tse

	* configure.in: fix again cygwin build failure unreleased
	regression

2008-11-25   Dan Fandrich

	* src/userauth.c: Fixed a potential use of an uninitialized
	variable, the result of which lead to an unneeded but harmless
	realloc.  Reduced the scope of some automatic variables.

2008-11-25   Dan Fandrich

	* src/publickey.c: Fixed some typos in log messages

2008-11-24  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, docs/Makefile.am, include/libssh2.h, src/kex.c,
	src/libssh2_priv.h, src/packet.c, src/session.c, src/transport.c:
	- Vlad Grachov brought the new function called
	  libssh2_session_block_directions() which returns a bitmask for
	  what directions the connection blocks. It is to be used
	  applications that use non-blocking sockets and when a libssh2
	  function returns LIBSSH2_ERROR_EAGAIN this function can be used to
	  figure out in which direction the socket would block and thus it can
	  wait for the socket to again be ready for communication in that
	  direction before it calls libssh2 again.

2008-11-21  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* NEWS, configure.in, tests/Makefile.am, tests/ssh2.c,
	tests/ssh2.sh, tests/sshdwrap, tests/etc/host, tests/etc/host.pub,
	tests/etc/sshd_config, tests/etc/user, tests/etc/user.pub: Add a
	more realistic self-test of libssh2.

2008-11-21  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* Makefile.am: Add rules to generate a code coverage report.

2008-11-21  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* example/simple/Makefile.am, src/Makefile.am: Use AM_CPPFLAGS
	instead of deprecated INCLUDES.

2008-11-21  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* tests/simple.c: Add self-test of base64 decode.

2008-11-21   Dan Fandrich

	* src/session.c: Use only C89-style comments

2008-11-21   Dan Fandrich

	* src/mac.c: Check LIBSSH2_HMAC_RIPEMD consistently

2008-11-20  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* src/libgcrypt.c, src/libgcrypt.h, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/pem.c:
	Fix compiler warnings.

2008-11-20  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* src/Makefile.am: Move pem.c to libgcrypt section, it is not
	needed for OpenSSL.

2008-11-19  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* configure.in: Drop pkg-config test, not needed now.

2008-11-19  Simon Josefsson <simon@josefsson.org>

	* NEWS, README, configure.in, src/Makefile.am: Rewrite OpenSSL+libz
	detection logic.

2008-11-11  Daniel Stenberg

	* example/simple/Makefile.am: fix the include path to also point
	out the build dir's src/ dir for the cases where we build the lot
	outside of the source dir

2008-11-11  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/libssh2_priv.h: avoid duplicate function declarations on
	windows

2008-11-10  Daniel Stenberg

	* win32/libssh2_config.h: WINSOCK_VERSION is no longer used
	(Richard W.M. Jones fixed)

2008-11-10  Daniel Stenberg

	* configure.in, example/simple/Makefile.am, example/simple/scp.c,
	example/simple/scp_nonblock.c, example/simple/scp_write.c,
	example/simple/scp_write_nonblock.c, example/simple/sftp.c,
	example/simple/sftp_RW_nonblock.c, example/simple/sftp_mkdir.c,
	example/simple/sftp_mkdir_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftp_nonblock.c, example/simple/sftp_write.c,
	example/simple/sftp_write_nonblock.c, example/simple/sftpdir.c,
	example/simple/sftpdir_nonblock.c, example/simple/ssh2.c,
	src/libssh2_priv.h: Richard W.M. Jones' 5 patches that enables
	libssh2 to get cross-compiled with mingw

2008-11-09   Paul Thomas

	* src/channel.c: Fixes a problem that the last code change
	apparently didn't fix. Verified that this works correctly with
	another user.

2008-11-01   Paul Thomas

	* src/channel.c: Fixed an issue with a patch that I submitted where
	the channel_read_ex() could get stuck in a busy read loop.

2008-10-25   Yang Tse

	* configure.in: fix cygwin build failure unreleased regression

2008-10-03   Paul Thomas

	* src/channel.c, src/session.c: Reformatted the code, updated line
	endings to match original file, fixed the build problem, removed
	 tabs and replaced with spaces and removed C89 unfriendly comments.

2008-10-02  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS: mention libssh2_channel_request_pty_size_ex()

2008-10-02   Paul Thomas

	* src/channel.c: This fix addresses bug# 2141548. Channel reads
	would fail despite libssh2_poll() detecting that there was data
	ready to be read on the socket. This is seen when small amounts of
	data are ready to be read, typically 1-4 chars worth.

2008-10-01   Paul Thomas

	* include/libssh2.h, src/channel.c: Committed changes to add in
	support for pty resizing. Credit for this patch goes to Vincent
	Jaulin.

2008-10-01   Paul Thomas

	* src/session.c: Fixed an issue with the libssh2_poll_channel_read
	function not reading both normal and extended data when a non-zero
	value is passed in as the 2nd parameter. This now matches the
	functionallity described in the documentation.

2008-09-30  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, configure.in, src/libssh2_priv.h, win32/libssh2_config.h:
	Carlo Bramini fixed the build for msys+mingw. Bug #1943976.

2008-09-30  Daniel Stenberg

	* example/simple/scp_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/scp_write_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftp_RW_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftp_mkdir_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftp_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftp_write_nonblock.c,
	example/simple/sftpdir_nonblock.c: Carlo Bramini's fixes for the
	nonblocking examples for msys/mingw

2008-09-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, win32/libssh2_config.h: Neil Gierman provided improved
	Visual Studio 2008 code in bug #1946268

2008-09-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/libssh2_priv.h, win32/libssh2_config.h:
	- Bug #1862727 fixed libssh2_poll() to work on windows (by defining
	HAVE_SELECT).

2008-09-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, docs/libssh2_sftp_seek.3, include/libssh2_sftp.h,
	src/sftp.c:
	- Based on bug #1815692, we introduce libssh2_sftp_seek2() that
	  allows seeking beyond the 2GB margin even on 32bit machines.

2008-09-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, configure.in, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/scp.c:
	- Based on a patch in bug #1878059 by Steven Ayre libssh2 now parses
	  >2GB file sizes when downloading SCP files.

2008-09-29  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, include/libssh2.h: Adhere to RFC4253 better and don't use
	dash in the banner string. Bug #2064371

2008-07-03  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/kex.c, src/libssh2_priv.h, src/packet.c,
	src/sshentry.c, src/transport.c: Sean Peterson's key re-exchange
	fix. See his long explanation on:

	http://daniel.haxx.se/projects/libssh2/mail/libssh2-devel-archive-2008-06/0002.shtml

2008-07-03  Daniel Stenberg

	* docs/libssh2_session_abstract.3,
	docs/libssh2_session_set_blocking.3: minor language updates

2008-06-24  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: Gah, I broke Sebastian's patch when I left out the
	parentheses his patch did contain. Added properly now.

2008-06-23  Daniel Stenberg

	* src/sftp.c: |sftp.c:1470: warning: cast to pointer from integer
	of different size Another reason why macros are evil: The string
	(which is allready char *) should be cast into char * not the
	integer.

	Signed-off-by: Sebastian Siewior <sebastian@breakpoint.cc>

2008-03-08  dottedmag

	* docs/Makefile.am,
	docs/libssh2_userauth_keyboard_interactive_ex.3: Added manpage for
	libssh2_userauth_keyboard_interactive_ex(3)

2008-03-07  Daniel Stenberg

	* NEWS, src/misc.c:
	- Mike Protts filed the bug report #1908724 that identified and
	  fixed a problem with SFTP stat on files >4GB in size. Previously it
	used 32bit math only.

